{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to share with you the story"},{"time":3000,"text":"as to how I have become"},{"time":5000,"text":"an HIV/AIDS campaigner."},{"time":8000,"text":"And this is the name of my campaign: SING Campaign."},{"time":12000,"text":"In November of 2003,"},{"time":14000,"text":"I was invited to take part"},{"time":16000,"text":"in the launch of Nelson Mandela's"},{"time":18000,"text":"46664 Foundation --"},{"time":21000,"text":"that is his HIV/AIDS foundation."},{"time":23000,"text":"And 46664 is the number"},{"time":25000,"text":"that Mandela had when he was imprisoned in Robben Island."},{"time":29000,"text":"And that's me with Youssou N'Dour,"},{"time":31000,"text":"onstage, having the time of my life."},{"time":36000,"text":"The next day, all the artists were invited"},{"time":38000,"text":"to join Mandela in Robben Island,"},{"time":41000,"text":"where he was going to give a conference"},{"time":43000,"text":"to the world's press,"},{"time":46000,"text":"standing in front of his former prison cell."},{"time":48000,"text":"You can see the bars of the window there."},{"time":51000,"text":"It was quite a momentous occasion for all of us."},{"time":54000,"text":"In that moment in time,"},{"time":56000,"text":"Mandela told the world's press"},{"time":59000,"text":"that there was a virtual genocide"},{"time":61000,"text":"taking place in his country;"},{"time":63000,"text":"that post-apartheid"},{"time":65000,"text":"Rainbow Nation,"},{"time":67000,"text":"a thousand people were dying on a daily basis"},{"time":70000,"text":"and that the front line victims,"},{"time":72000,"text":"the most vulnerable of all,"},{"time":74000,"text":"were women and children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"This was a huge impact on my mind,"},{"time":80000,"text":"because I am a woman and I am a mother,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and I hadn't realized"},{"time":85000,"text":"that the HIV/AIDS pandemic"},{"time":87000,"text":"was directly affecting women in such a way."},{"time":90000,"text":"And so I committed -- when I left South Africa,"},{"time":92000,"text":"when I left Capetown,"},{"time":94000,"text":"I told myself, \"This is going to be something"},{"time":96000,"text":"that I have to talk about."},{"time":98000,"text":"I have to serve.\""},{"time":100000,"text":"And so, subsequently"},{"time":102000,"text":"I participated in every single"},{"time":104000,"text":"46664 event"},{"time":106000,"text":"that I could take part in"},{"time":108000,"text":"and gave news conferences,"},{"time":110000,"text":"interviews,"},{"time":112000,"text":"talking and using my platform as a musician,"},{"time":115000,"text":"with my commitment to Mandela --"},{"time":117000,"text":"out of respect for the tremendous,"},{"time":120000,"text":"unbelievable work that he had done."},{"time":122000,"text":"Everyone in the world respects Nelson Mandela,"},{"time":125000,"text":"everyone reveres Nelson Mandela."},{"time":127000,"text":"But do they all know"},{"time":129000,"text":"about what has been taking place in South Africa,"},{"time":131000,"text":"his country,"},{"time":134000,"text":"the country that had one of the highest incidents"},{"time":136000,"text":"of transmission of the virus?"},{"time":138000,"text":"I think that if I went out into the street now"},{"time":141000,"text":"and I told people what was happening there,"},{"time":143000,"text":"they would be shocked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"I was very, very fortunate a couple of years later"},{"time":149000,"text":"to have met Zackie Achmat,"},{"time":151000,"text":"the founder of Treatment Action Campaign,"},{"time":153000,"text":"an incredible campaigner and activist."},{"time":156000,"text":"I met him at a 46664 event."},{"time":158000,"text":"He was wearing a t-shirt like the one I wear now."},{"time":160000,"text":"This is a tool --"},{"time":162000,"text":"this tells you I am in solidarity"},{"time":164000,"text":"with people who have HIV,"},{"time":167000,"text":"people who are living with HIV."},{"time":169000,"text":"And in a way because of the stigma, by wearing this t-shirt"},{"time":172000,"text":"I say, \"Yes, we can talk about this issue."},{"time":175000,"text":"It doesn't have to be in the closet.\""},{"time":178000,"text":"I became a member of Treatment Action Campaign"},{"time":181000,"text":"and I'm very proud to be a member"},{"time":183000,"text":"of that incredible organization."},{"time":185000,"text":"It's a grassroots campaign"},{"time":187000,"text":"with 80 percent membership being women,"},{"time":190000,"text":"most of whom are HIV-positive."},{"time":193000,"text":"They work in the field."},{"time":195000,"text":"They have tremendous outreach"},{"time":198000,"text":"to the people who are living directly"},{"time":200000,"text":"with the effects of the virus."},{"time":202000,"text":"They have education programs."},{"time":205000,"text":"They bring out the issues of stigma."},{"time":208000,"text":"It's quite extraordinary what they do."},{"time":211000,"text":"And yes, my SING Campaign"},{"time":213000,"text":"has supported Treatment Action Campaign"},{"time":215000,"text":"in the way that I have tried to raise awareness"},{"time":218000,"text":"and to try to also raise funds."},{"time":220000,"text":"A lot of the funding that I have managed to raise"},{"time":222000,"text":"has gone directly to Treatment Action Campaign"},{"time":224000,"text":"and the incredible work that they do,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and are still continuing to do in South Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"So this is my SING Campaign."},{"time":231000,"text":"SING Campaign is basically just me"},{"time":233000,"text":"and about three or four wonderful people"},{"time":235000,"text":"who help to support me."},{"time":237000,"text":"I've traveled all over the world"},{"time":239000,"text":"in the last two and a half years --"},{"time":241000,"text":"I went to about 12 different countries."},{"time":243000,"text":"Here I am in Oslo in Norway,"},{"time":245000,"text":"getting a nice, fat check;"},{"time":248000,"text":"singing in Hong Kong, trying to get people to raise money."},{"time":251000,"text":"In Johannesburg, I had the opportunity to play"},{"time":254000,"text":"to a mainly white, middle-class South African audience"},{"time":256000,"text":"who ended up in tears"},{"time":258000,"text":"because I use film clips"},{"time":260000,"text":"that really touch the heart, the whole nature,"},{"time":262000,"text":"of this terrible tragedy that is taking place,"},{"time":265000,"text":"that people are tending to avoid,"},{"time":267000,"text":"because they are fatigued,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and they really don't quite know what the solutions are."},{"time":272000,"text":"Aaron Motsoaledi, the current health minister,"},{"time":274000,"text":"attended that concert"},{"time":276000,"text":"and I had an opportunity to meet with him,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and he gave his absolute commitment"},{"time":280000,"text":"to try to making a change,"},{"time":282000,"text":"which is absolutely necessary."},{"time":284000,"text":"This is in the Scottish Parliament."},{"time":286000,"text":"I've subsequently become an envoy"},{"time":288000,"text":"for Scotland and HIV."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I was showing them my experiences"},{"time":292000,"text":"and trying to, again, raise awareness."},{"time":295000,"text":"And once again, in Edinburgh"},{"time":297000,"text":"with the wonderful African Children's Choir who I simply adore."},{"time":300000,"text":"And it's children like this, many of whom have been orphaned"},{"time":303000,"text":"because of their family being affected"},{"time":306000,"text":"by the AIDS virus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"I'm sitting here in New York with Michel Sidibe --"},{"time":311000,"text":"he's the director of UNAIDS."},{"time":313000,"text":"And I'm very honored"},{"time":315000,"text":"by the fact that Michel invited me,"},{"time":317000,"text":"only a few months ago,"},{"time":319000,"text":"to become a UNAIDS ambassador."},{"time":321000,"text":"And in this way, I've been strengthening my platform"},{"time":324000,"text":"and broadening my outreach."},{"time":326000,"text":"The message that UNAIDS"},{"time":328000,"text":"are currently sending out to the world"},{"time":330000,"text":"is that we would like to see the virtual elimination"},{"time":333000,"text":"of the transmission of the virus"},{"time":335000,"text":"from mother to child by 2015."},{"time":338000,"text":"It's a very ambitious goal"},{"time":340000,"text":"but we believe it can be achieved with political will."},{"time":343000,"text":"This can happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And here I am with a pregnant woman,"},{"time":347000,"text":"who is HIV positive"},{"time":349000,"text":"and we're smiling, both of us are smiling, because we're very confident,"},{"time":352000,"text":"because we know that that young woman"},{"time":355000,"text":"is receiving treatment"},{"time":357000,"text":"so her life can be extended"},{"time":359000,"text":"to take care of the baby she's about to give birth to."},{"time":362000,"text":"And her baby will receive PMTCT,"},{"time":365000,"text":"which will mean that that baby"},{"time":367000,"text":"can be born free of the virus."},{"time":369000,"text":"Now that is prevention"},{"time":371000,"text":"at the very beginning of life."},{"time":373000,"text":"It's one way to start looking at intervention"},{"time":376000,"text":"with the AIDS pandemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"Now, I just would like to finish off"},{"time":380000,"text":"to tell you the little story"},{"time":382000,"text":"about Avelile."},{"time":384000,"text":"This is Avelile --"},{"time":386000,"text":"she goes with me wherever I go."},{"time":388000,"text":"I tell her story to everyone"},{"time":390000,"text":"because she represents"},{"time":392000,"text":"one of millions"},{"time":394000,"text":"of HIV/AIDS orphans."},{"time":396000,"text":"Avelile's mother"},{"time":398000,"text":"had HIV virus --"},{"time":400000,"text":"she died"},{"time":402000,"text":"from AIDS-related illness."},{"time":404000,"text":"Avelile had the virus,"},{"time":406000,"text":"she was born with the virus."},{"time":408000,"text":"And here she is at seven years old,"},{"time":411000,"text":"weighing no more than a one year-old baby."},{"time":413000,"text":"At this point in her life,"},{"time":415000,"text":"she's suffering with full-blown AIDS"},{"time":417000,"text":"and had pneumonia."},{"time":419000,"text":"We met her in a hospital in the Eastern Cape"},{"time":422000,"text":"and spent a whole afternoon with her -- an adorable child."},{"time":425000,"text":"The doctors and nurses were phenomenal."},{"time":427000,"text":"They put her on very special nutritious diet"},{"time":430000,"text":"and took great care of her."},{"time":433000,"text":"And we didn't know when we left the hospital --"},{"time":435000,"text":"because we filmed her story -- we didn't know if she was going to survive."},{"time":438000,"text":"So, it was obviously -- it was a very emotional encounter"},{"time":441000,"text":"and left us feeling very resonant"},{"time":443000,"text":"with this direct experience, this one child,"},{"time":446000,"text":"you know, that story."},{"time":448000,"text":"Five months later,"},{"time":451000,"text":"we went back to South Africa"},{"time":453000,"text":"to meet Avelile again."},{"time":456000,"text":"And I'm getting --"},{"time":458000,"text":"the hairs on my -- I don't know if you can see the hairs on my arms."},{"time":460000,"text":"They're standing up because I know what I'm going to show you."},{"time":463000,"text":"This is the transformation that took place."},{"time":468000,"text":"Isn't it extraordinary?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"That round of applause is actually"},{"time":482000,"text":"for the doctors and nurses of the hospital who took care of Avelile."},{"time":485000,"text":"And I take it that you appreciate that kind of transformation."},{"time":489000,"text":"So, I would like to say to you,"},{"time":491000,"text":"each one in the audience,"},{"time":493000,"text":"if you feel that every mother"},{"time":496000,"text":"and every child in the world"},{"time":498000,"text":"has the right to have access"},{"time":500000,"text":"to good nutrition and good medical care,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and you believe that the Millennium Development Goals,"},{"time":506000,"text":"specifically five and six,"},{"time":508000,"text":"should be absolutely committed to"},{"time":511000,"text":"by all governments around the world --"},{"time":513000,"text":"especially in sub-Saharan Africa --"},{"time":515000,"text":"could you please stand up."},{"time":523000,"text":"I think that's fair to say,"},{"time":525000,"text":"it's almost everyone in the hall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}